  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Tamil Nadu Housing Board, Rep. by its Managing Director and Ors. versus S. Ganesan pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_7_1530_1537','2025INSC889'); ><font size='4'> <strong>TAMIL NADU HOUSING BOARD, REP. BY ITS MANAGING DIRECTOR AND ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>S. GANESAN </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 1530</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 889</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008012025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the facts and circumstances of the case, the High Court was justified in directing the sale deed of the plot to be executed in favour of the respondent subject to the fulfilment of the condition stated. Headnotes&dagger; Public Property &ndash; Occupied for over three decades despite defaults in making the balance payment therefor &ndash; Long-drawn litigation &ndash; High Court directed the sale deed of the plot to be executed in favour of the respondent on payment of Rs.3 crore in three monthly instalments despite noting that the market<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9631/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_7_1530_1537','2025INSC889','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'>